# PPE desktop vs VM (agents — hard)

**Canon:** [`PPE_OPERATOR_LAYOUT_ADR.md`](docs/SOP/PPE_OPERATOR_LAYOUT_ADR.md) · [`PPE_CANONICAL_OPERATOR_SCRIPTS_V1.md`](docs/SOP/PPE_CANONICAL_OPERATOR_SCRIPTS_V1.md) (verdict SSOT)

## Machine roles

| Machine | Relay / loop | Product BUILD | After IDE BUILD |
|---------|----------------|---------------|-----------------|
| **Hyper-V VM** (`PPE_LOOP_HOST=1`) | **Yes** — headless stack, auto loop | No (blocks → `IDE_BUILD`) | Automatic in loop |
| **Daily desktop** (`PPE_STACK_FORBIDDEN` or no loop token) | **Never** | **Yes** — Cursor IDE BUILD | **`DESKTOP_CONTINUE.cmd`** (SSH → VM `finish_ide_build.cmd`) |

Reading `OPERATOR_STATUS.md` / `ppe_operator_status.py` is fine on **operator** threads (either machine). **Charter/topic threads:** do not read unless switching role ([`ppe-thread-roles.mdc`](ppe-thread-roles.mdc)). **Executing relay** is VM-only.

## Before any relay command (mandatory)

Run **first**:

```bash
python scripts/ppe_loop_host_guard.py --check
```

If `"allowed": false` → **do not** run relay locally. Map verdict using [`PPE_CANONICAL_OPERATOR_SCRIPTS_V1.md`](docs/SOP/PPE_CANONICAL_OPERATOR_SCRIPTS_V1.md).

## Forbidden on daily desktop (never run in Cursor shell)

- `run_ppe_local.cmd` / `run_ppe.cmd`
- `run_ppe_auto_local_loop.cmd` / `run_ppe_auto_loop.cmd`
- `run_ppe_headless_stack.cmd`
- `ppe_autobuilder.cmd advance` (relay advance)
- `finish_ide_build.cmd` (VM one-shot — desktop uses `DESKTOP_CONTINUE.cmd` instead)

**Why:** Desktop lacks ACP orchestrator path and is not the loop host; these fail or fight the VM supervisor.

## Verdict → agent action

Full table: [`PPE_CANONICAL_OPERATOR_SCRIPTS_V1.md`](docs/SOP/PPE_CANONICAL_OPERATOR_SCRIPTS_V1.md). Quick reference:

| Verdict | Desktop | VM |
|---------|---------|-----|
| `IDE_BUILD` | Implement slice; gate → commit → `mark_ide_product_ready` | Wait for desktop BUILD |
| `RUN_LOCAL` | **`DESKTOP_CONTINUE.cmd`** (after merge) | `run_ppe_local.cmd` |
| `RUN_AUTO` | SSH status only | `run_ppe.cmd` or loop advance |

## SSH status (desktop agents)

**Budget:** one SSH call per operator pass; 120s max; no parallel sessions; no SSH+findstr on repo JSON (read locally).

```bash
python scripts/ppe_operator_status.py --brief
```

Optional VM brief (only when mirror stale): use `scripts/ppe_operator_vm_ssh.py` via `DESKTOP_CONTINUE.cmd` or:

```bash
ssh -o BatchMode=yes -o ConnectTimeout=15 -o ServerAliveInterval=10 -o ServerAliveCountMax=3 ppeloop@desktop-caqll8k "cd /d C:\Users\ppeloop\Probability-prediction-engine && ppe_autobuilder.cmd status --brief"
```

**Prefer git mirror:** `docs/SOP/VM_OPERATOR_PHASE.json` (VM loop host writes; desktop `git pull`).

**Canonical SSH wrapper:** `scripts/ppe_operator_vm_ssh.py` — all agent/desktop Python paths must use this, not raw `subprocess.run(["ssh", ...])`.

## Common mistake (do not repeat)

`RUN_LOCAL` on desktop **≠** `run_ppe_local.cmd`. It **always** means **`DESKTOP_CONTINUE.cmd`** unless `ppe_loop_host_guard.py --check` reports `"allowed": true`.
